ZCZC OE49
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 152300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL BE
CENTRED NEAR TO ICELAND 955 WITH ASSOCIATED FRONTAL
TROUGHS AFFECTING THE UK. BY MIDDAY WEDNESDAY THIS LOW
MOVS TO THE N OF ICELAND TO ALLOW A NEW DPN LOW TO
APPROACH THE UK FM THE ATLANTIC CENTRED TO THE W OF
ROCKALL 961. THIS SECOND LOW MOVS NEWARDS AND DEEPENS
TO BE CENTRED TO THE NW OF SCOTLAND 955 BY MIDNIGHT
MOV TOWARDS ICELAND BY MIDDAY THURSDAY 950. A TRANSIENT
RIDGE AFFECTS THE UK ON FRIDAY AHEAD OF ANOTHER LOW
PRESSURE IN THE MID-ATLANTIC MOV TOWARDS THE UK WITH
ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGHS REACHING THE UK BY THE END OF
FRIDAY. THIS WILL BE A VERY WINDY PERIOD ACROSS
PORTPATRICK. GALES OR SEV GALES WILL AFFECT ALL AREAS
WITH STORM FORCE WINDS DEVELOPING IN PARTS TUESDAY NIGHT
INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING THEN AGAIN WEDNESDAY NIGHT
